The <b>Valhalla Matrix</b> algorithm calculates origin-destination matrices for two input layers by calculating routes from each point in layer 1 to each point in layer 2. Specifying the same layer twice will result in a cross product of that layer.

Specify points and/or polygons to be avoided with the <i>avoid locations</i> / <i>polygons</i> parameters.
The output layer is a table layer with the attributes <i>durations</i>, <i>distances</i>, and <i>ID</i>.

Valhalla has a dynamic cost model. You can set an extensive amount of costing options in the <b>Advanced Parameters</b> section. Refer to
<a href="https://github.com/valhalla/valhalla/blob/master/docs/api/turn-by-turn/api-reference.md">the documentation</a> for an in-depth explanation.
